  "metadata": {
    "what_it_measures": "Quarterly measure of total compensation costs for civilian workers. Fed's preferred wage gauge. Released end of January, April, July, October.\n",
    "why_it_matters": "Wages are the biggest input cost for services inflation. The Fed watches ECI closely \u2014 if wage growth stays above ~3.5% annualized, services inflation is hard to bring to 2%.\n",
    "scoring_rule": "Annualized: < 3.0% \u2192 +60 | 3.0-3.5% \u2192 +20 | 3.5-4.0% \u2192 -20 | 4.0-5.0% \u2192 -50 | > 5.0% \u2192 -80. Phase 3.\n"
  },
